📝 DRY-RUN PLAN — yage would perform the following actions
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

▸ Pre-phase
    • ClusterSetID = test-clusterset (identity suffix: <derived>)

▸ Dependency install — host CLIs for the operator
    • system packages: git, curl, python3 (apt/dnf/yum/apk)
    • Docker: install if missing; upgrade unless --no-delete-kind or kind cluster exists
    • kubectl      v1.32.0    (install)
    • kind         v0.24.0    (install)
    • clusterctl   v1.8.5     (install)
    • cilium       v0.16.20   (install)
    • helm         latest     (install)
    • argocd       v2.13.2    (install)
    • kyverno      v1.13.2    (install)
    • cmctl        v2.1.1     (install)
    • tofu         1.8.5      (install)

▸ Identity bootstrap — AWS IAM
    ◦ skip: AWS uses operator-supplied IAM (env: AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID / _SECRET_ACCESS_KEY / AWS_PROFILE)
    ◦ skip: CAPA bootstrap stack created out-of-band — `clusterawsadm bootstrap iam create-cloudformation-stack`

▸ clusterctl credentials
    • synthesize ephemeral clusterctl config from Proxmox env (URL/TOKEN/SECRET)

▸ kind cluster
    • create kind cluster 'capi-test' (config: <ephemeral default>)

▸ clusterctl init on kind
    • providers: infrastructure=aws, ipam=in-cluster, addon=helm
    • CAPMOX image: v0.7.0 (build arm64 if needed)

▸ Workload Cluster — AWS (mode: unmanaged)
    • Cluster: default/capi-quickstart, k8s v1.32.0, region us-east-1
    • control plane: 1 × t3.large, 30 GB gp3 root, ssh-key=<unset>, ami=<auto-resolved>
    • workers: 2 × t3.medium, 40 GB gp3 root
    • overhead tier: prod (NAT GW / ALB / egress / CW logs counts → see Cost section)
    ◦ skip: Proxmox CSI (AWS uses aws-ebs-csi-driver via Helm + IRSA — out of scope for yage)

▸ Pivot to managed mgmt cluster
    ◦ skip: AWS provider has no PivotTarget yet (kind remains the mgmt cluster)

▸ Argo CD on workload
    • Argo CD Operator + ArgoCD CR (version v2.13.2, operator v0.12.2)
    • CAAPH argocd-apps HelmChartProxy → root Application 'capi-quickstart'
    •   app-of-apps: https://github.com/example/app-of-apps @ main, path apps

▸ Final — kind teardown
    ◦ skip: PIVOT_ENABLED=false (kind stays — it IS the management cluster)

▸ Capacity budget
    • budget: 75% of available host CPU/memory/storage
    •   workload control-plane     1 × (1 cores, 0 MiB, 30 GB) = 1 cores, 0 MiB, 30 GB
    •   workload worker            2 × (1 cores, 0 MiB, 40 GB) = 2 cores, 0 MiB, 80 GB
    • TOTAL requested:  3 cores, 0 MiB (0 GiB), 110 GB disk
    ◦ skip: provider "aws" has no flat-pool inventory model — preflight skipped (§13.4 #1)

▸ Workload allocations (per-bucket budget on workers)
    • total worker capacity:    2000 millicores, 0 MiB (workers=2 ×  sockets ×  cores ×  MiB)
    • system-apps reserve:      2000 millicores, 4096 MiB
    •   ├─ argocd (operator + server + repo + redis), kyverno, cert-manager,
    •   ├─ proxmox-csi (controller), keycloak (SSO), external-secrets, infisical
    •   └─ tune via SYSTEM_APPS_CPU_MILLICORES / SYSTEM_APPS_MEMORY_MIB
    • ❌ system reserve (2000 mCPU / 4096 MiB) exceeds total worker capacity (2000 / 0)
    •    grow worker count / sizing, OR untaint the control-plane node and let it host system pods
